<h2>Materials</h2>
<p>We use <strong>3M and Avery Dennison wall-rated vinyl</strong> specifically designed for interior and exterior architectural surfaces:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>3M IJ180mC-10</strong> — cast vinyl with high-tack adhesive for textured drywall and concrete</li>
<li><strong>Avery Dennison MPI 2611</strong> — wall vinyl rated for smooth and lightly textured surfaces</li>
<li><strong>3M Envision 48C</strong> — PVC-free wall vinyl for LEED-certified and eco-conscious spaces</li>
<li><strong>UV-resistant overlaminate</strong> — standard on exterior installations for 5–7 year durability</li>
<li><strong>Anti-graffiti laminate</strong> — optional protection for public-facing exterior wraps</li>
</ul>

<h2>Surfaces We Wrap</h2>
<p>We've installed wall graphics on every surface type found in Chicago commercial buildings:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Painted drywall</strong> — the most common interior surface. Clean, smooth application.</li>
<li><strong>Concrete block</strong> — textured surface requires high-tack adhesive vinyl</li>
<li><strong>Brick</strong> — interior exposed brick walls. Specialty materials required.</li>
<li><strong>Glass</strong> — window graphics, frosted privacy film, and perforated vinyl</li>
<li><strong>Metal panels</strong> — elevator doors, column wraps, and metal wall panels</li>
<li><strong>Wood paneling</strong> — smooth or lightly textured wood surfaces</li>
</ul>

