<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>How much do wall wraps cost?</h3><p>Logo walls start at $500. Full wall murals range from $1,200–$5,000. Large commercial installations can run $5,000–$20,000+. Pricing depends on wall size, surface, and design complexity.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>Can you wrap textured walls?</h3><p>Yes. We use high-tack adhesive vinyl designed for textured surfaces including drywall, concrete block, and stucco.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>How long do wall wraps last?</h3><p>Interior: 7–10+ years. Exterior: 5–7 years with UV overlaminate. Indoor wraps see minimal wear and often last the life of the space.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>Can wall wraps be removed?</h3><p>Yes. Quality wall vinyl is removable. Wall prep quality affects removal — well-primed walls see cleaner removal.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>Do you install on-site?</h3><p>Yes. All wall wrap installations are done on-site at your location. We serve all of Chicagoland.</p></div>

